## 4. Media Storage Architecture (S3 + CloudFront)

### 4.1 S3 Bucket Design

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                     S3 BUCKET ARCHITECTURE                       │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│                                                                 │
│  Each bucket follows identical structure:                       │
│                                                                 │
│  nuttyfans-media-{env}/                                         │
│  ├── uploads/              # Temporary uploads (pre-processing) │
│  │   └── {year}/{month}/{day}/{uuid}/                          │
│  ├── media/                                                     │
│  │   ├── images/           # Processed images                   │
│  │   │   └── {creator_id}/{post_id}/{size}/                    │
│  │   ├── videos/           # Processed videos                   │
│  │   │   └── {creator_id}/{post_id}/{quality}/                 │
│  │   └── thumbnails/       # Generated thumbnails               │
│  │       └── {creator_id}/{post_id}/                           │
│  ├── avatars/              # User/creator profile images        │
│  │   └── {user_id}/                                            │
│  ├── covers/               # Creator cover images               │
│  │   └── {creator_id}/                                         │
│  └── documents/            # KYC documents (encrypted)          │
│      └── {user_id}/                                            │
│                                                                 │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

### 4.2 S3 Security Configuration

| Setting | Value | Rationale |
|---------|-------|-----------|
| **Public Access** | `BLOCK ALL` | Security — CDN only access |
| **Encryption** | `SSE-S3` (AES-256) | Data at rest protection |
| **Versioning** | `Disabled` (initially) | Cost optimization |
| **Lifecycle Rules** | `uploads/` → 7 day expiry | Clean up incomplete uploads |
| **Access Logging** | `Disabled` (initially) | Cost optimization; enable for audit if needed |

### 4.3 S3 Bucket Policy (CDN-Only Access)

```json
{
  "Version": "2012-10-17",
  "Statement": [
    {
      "Sid": "AllowCloudFrontServicePrincipal",
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Principal": {
        "Service": "cloudfront.amazonaws.com"
      },
      "Action": "s3:GetObject",
      "Resource": "arn:aws:s3:::nuttyfans-media-{env}/*",
      "Condition": {
        "StringEquals": {
          "AWS:SourceArn": "arn:aws:cloudfront::{account-id}:distribution/{distribution-id}"
        }
      }
    }
  ]
}
```

**Critical:** This policy ensures S3 objects are ONLY accessible via CloudFront. Direct S3 access will return 403 Forbidden.

### 4.4 CloudFront Distribution Configuration

| Setting | Value | Rationale |
|---------|-------|-----------|
| **Origin** | S3 bucket (OAC) | Security via Origin Access Control |
| **Origin Access** | OAC (not OAI) | AWS recommended approach |
| **Price Class** | `PriceClass_100` | US/Canada/Europe only (cost saving) |
| **Cache Policy** | `CachingOptimized` | Standard caching for static assets |
| **Viewer Protocol** | `HTTPS only` | Security |
| **HTTP Version** | `HTTP/2` | Performance |
| **Compress** | `Yes` | Performance (gzip/brotli) |
| **Custom Error Pages** | 403 → 404 | Hide bucket existence from probing |

