### 5.2 GitHub Actions Workflow Specification

**File:** `.github/workflows/ci.yml`

```yaml
name: CI

on:
  push:
    branches: [dev, qa, main]
  pull_request:
    branches: [dev, qa, main]

concurrency:
  group: ${{ github.workflow }}-${{ github.ref }}
  cancel-in-progress: true

jobs:
  quality:
    name: Quality Checks
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    timeout-minutes: 10

    steps:
      - name: Checkout
        uses: actions/checkout@v4

      - name: Setup pnpm
        uses: pnpm/action-setup@v3
        with:
          version: 9

      - name: Setup Node.js
        uses: actions/setup-node@v4
        with:
          node-version: '20'
          cache: 'pnpm'

      - name: Install dependencies
        run: pnpm install --frozen-lockfile

      - name: Lint
        run: pnpm lint

      - name: Type check
        run: pnpm typecheck

      - name: Build
        run: pnpm build
        env:
          # Provide dummy values for build-time env vars
          DATABASE_URL: "postgresql://dummy:dummy@localhost:5432/dummy"
```

### 5.3 Workflow Optimization (Private Repo)

| Optimization | Implementation | Savings |
|--------------|----------------|---------|
| **Dependency Caching** | `cache: 'pnpm'` in setup-node | ~2-3 min/run |
| **Concurrency Control** | `cancel-in-progress: true` | Avoid redundant runs |
| **Timeout** | `timeout-minutes: 10` | Prevent stuck jobs |
| **Frozen Lockfile** | `--frozen-lockfile` | Faster, more reliable installs |

**Estimated Run Time:** 4-6 minutes per run  
**Monthly Budget (2000 min):** ~300-500 runs/month

